Describe the differences between forks, clones, and branches.  When would you
use one instead of another?

    forks: copy from github to github
    clone: copy from github or local directory to local directory
    branch: create a new part of the project.

What is the benefit of having a copy of the last known state of the remote
stored locally?

    I can modify it locally and try some experimental changes while not influencing
    the github version.

How would you collaborate without using Git or GitHub?  What would be easier,
and what would be harder?

    Obviously it makes our life easy by using a Git or GitHub, especially when
    the collaboration happens all over the world.

